### Login
# Authenticates a user and returns a long-lived auth JWT.
# Public endpoint — no Authorization header required.
# Use the returned token as JWT_TOKEN in your env for authenticated requests.
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "change-me-on-first-login"
}

###

### Create User
# Creates a new user and returns a signup link containing a short-lived JWT.
# The signup link should be sent to the new user so they can set their password.
# Requires a valid Bearer JWT (auth token) in Authorization header.
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/create-user
Authorization: Bearer {{JWT_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "name": "New User"
}

###

### Set Password
# Sets the new user's password using the signup token from the signup link.
# Returns a long-lived auth JWT on success.
# Requires the signup token (from the signup link) in Authorization header.
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/set-password
Authorization: Bearer {{SIGNUP_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "password": "mysecurepassword",
  "confirmPassword": "mysecurepassword"
}
